    "If the similarity score falls between the 0.4 and 0.8 thresholds, the back-translated tweet is added to the new augmented dataset.",
    "The newly generated tweets are then merged with the original tweets to create the augmented dataset.",
    "Table 2 presents the statistics of the augmented dataset, while Table 3 provides three examples of the newly generated tweets.",
    "The final step involves classifying tweets as either fake or not fake using the pre-trained Arabic-Bert model.",
    "Arabic-Bert is selected for its high performance in detecting Arabic fake tweets (Refai et al. 2022)."
